    <div class="contentBox">
        <h3>Why do I like trains?</h3>
        <p>
            This is a very hard question to answer, I have liked trains for as long as I can remember. When I was young I loved Thomas the Tank Engine and as I got older I wanted to be a train driver. I'd say the biggest thing that got me obsessed was the railway museum in York, we would visit it quite often when I growing. I also find the fact that these huge incredibly complicated machines with slippery steel wheels on slippery steel track can move fascinating. Trains are also very good for the environment, they produce a tiny amount of C02 compared to cars, buses and trucks. Its weird that a thing that you wouldn't think could move with how heavy they are (and as I said before how slippery the tracks and wheels are) can be so efficient for moving large amounts of things, to the point that governments around the world are back tracking and building/re-opening train lines all over the place.<br />
            There is also a lot of nostalgia in trains for me, growing up my parents didn't drive and in fact still don't today, so they heavily relied on public transport to get around. With the fastest (and at the time, normally the cheapest) way to travel without a car.  They always told me that it was so much cheaper its why we could go on 2 holidays a year. The way we got everywhere was on the train. <br />
            I am still learning to drive while I write this(March 2024), many people tell me I should get a car as it would save me so much time, but the time spent on the train doesn't bother me. Probably partly because I became so used it, but also because I just like trains. People tell me my life will be easier with a car, but how could a thing that will cost me 4 times as much (I did calculate it using some back of the napkin maths) make my life easier, it would just re shape the way I think about and spend money to keep the car running. Now I don't need to worry about having money to buy petrol or new tyres, just at the start of the month buy a monthly bus ticket and any trains I know I will need, then I can get where I need to go without worry.
        </p>
